                <h1>When Was Rutgers Founded? A Brief History</h1>
                <p>Rutgers University, the eighth oldest institution of higher education in the United States, was founded in 1766. Initially established as Queen's College in New Brunswick, New Jersey, it was named Rutgers College in 1825 after Colonel Henry Rutgers, a prominent benefactor. Over the years, it has grown into a prestigious research university.</p>
